    <description>
Empirica is an epistemic self-assessment framework for AI agents. It provides:

- 4-phase CASCADE workflow (PREFLIGHT → CHECK → POSTFLIGHT → POST-TEST)
- Dual-track calibration (self-referential + grounded verification)
- 13-vector epistemic state tracking with Bayesian belief updates
- Goal orchestration with dependency management
- Git-based session checkpoints and handoff reports
- MCP (Model Context Protocol) server integration
- Qdrant semantic memory (eidetic facts, episodic narratives, pattern retrieval)

Perfect for AI agents that need genuine metacognitive awareness and calibration.
    </description>
    <summary>Epistemic self-assessment framework for AI agents with CASCADE workflow</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
Release 1.5.0 (Grounded Calibration):
- Dual-track calibration: self-referential (PREFLIGHT→POSTFLIGHT) + grounded (POSTFLIGHT→evidence)
- 4-phase CASCADE: PREFLIGHT → CHECK → POSTFLIGHT → POST-TEST (automatic)
- PostTestCollector: 6 evidence sources (pytest, git, goals, artifacts, issues, sentinel)
- EvidenceMapper with quality-weighted vector estimation
- GroundedCalibrationManager with parallel Bayesian tracking
- CalibrationTrajectory for trend detection (closing/widening/stable)
- 4 new verification schema tables
- CLI: calibration-report --grounded, calibration-report --trajectory
- 3,220+ calibration observations

Release 1.0.3 (Patch):
- MCP moved to optional dependencies
- Better package separation between empirica and empirica-mcp

Release 1.0.0 (Stable):
- MCO system with persona support
- Complete CASCADE workflow (PREFLIGHT/CHECK/POSTFLIGHT)
- Unified storage via GitEnhancedReflexLogger
- Project bootstrap with uncertainty-driven context loading
    </releaseNotes>
    <tags>ai llm epistemic metacognition self-assessment calibration python cli</tags>
